THE TRIGEN COMPANIES OWN AND OPERATE THE LARGEST PORTFOLIO OF DISTRICT ENERGY SYSTEMS IN THE U.S. AND THEY OPERATE FACILITIES IN 11 U.S. CITIES.  VEOLIA ENERGY BOUGHT TRIGEN IN 2007.  DISTRICT ENERGY SYSTEMS PROVIDE CHILLED WATER, STEAM, AND HOT WATER AND ALSO COGENERATES ELECTRICITY.

CONTINUATION: COUCH DRIVE IS NAMED FOR WILLIAM COUCH, OKLAHOMA CITY'S FIRST MAYOR (APR 1889-NOV 1889).  THE PARALLEL LANES OF COUCH DRIVE AND THE CENTRAL PARK SPACE WERE INTRODUCED BETWEEN 1930 AND 1949 AFTER THE CHICAGO, ROCK ISLAND & PACIFIC RAILWAY TRACKS THAT RAN THERE WERE DISCONTINUED AND REMOVED IN 1930-31.  THE LAYOUT OF THE PARK WAS PART OF THE DOWNTOWN CIVIC CENTER PLAN DESIGNED BY HARE & HARE IN THE EARLY 1930S.  THE FOUNTAIN/PADDLE WHEEL SCULPTURE APPEARS IN A 1976 PHOTOGRAPH.

Projectname: RECON. SURVEY: CENTRAL OKC; HERITAGE HILLS EAST SURVEY
EXTER_FEA: 1 STORY; SYMMETRICAL FACADE; 2 RECTANGULAR PROJECTIONS ON EAST ELEVATION ROOFED WITH INTERSECTING GABLES, 1 ON WEST ELEVATION; FULL-WIDTH FRONT PORCH COVERED
DEC_DETAIL: GABLE END INFILL LOOKS LIKE OVERSIZE LATTICE WITH SOLID BACKING, PORCH RAILING IS IDENTICAL EXCEPT LACKS BACKING; PORCH ROOF SUPPORTED BY MASSIVE TRUNCATED, RECTANGULAR TAPERED WOOD COLUMNS ON MASSIVE BATTERED STUCCO PIERS; HEADER BELOW PORCH GABLE END CURVES DOWN ONTO TOP OF WOOD COLUMNS; END WALL AND INTERIOR CHIMNEYS WITH CORBELED CAPS ON WEST SIDE
DES_RES: SINGLE STORY CRAFTSMAN WITH WOOD SIDING.  SYMMETRICAL FACADE.  ONE STEP LEADS UP TO THE FULL-WIDTH ENTRY PORCH, WHICH IS COVERED BY THE MAIN FRONT GABLE, WHICH HAS EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS AND AN OVERSIZED LATTICE INFILL AT THE GABLE END.  THE ROOF IS SUPPORTED BY FOUR LARGE TAPERED WOOD PIERS, WHICH ARE BOLSTERED BY MASSIVE BATTERED STUCCO PIERS.  THE HEADER BELOW THE PORCH GABLE CURVES DOWN ONTO TOP OF WOOD PIERS.  A LATTICE RAILING RUNS BETWEEN THE STUCCO PIERS AND PARTIALLY ENCLOSES THE PORCH.  THE CENTRAL DOOR IS FLANKED ON EITHER SIDE BY A PAIR OF 15/1 HUNG WINDOWS WITH WIDE TRIM.    ALTERATIONS: NONE.
COMMENTS: 41. DECORATIVE DETAILS, CONT.: MOLDING ABOVE WINDOWS AND DOORS.

Projectname: DOWNTOWN OKLAHOMA CITY INTENSIVE SURVEY - PHASE 1
EXTER_FEA: ONE-STORY BASE WITH SIX-STORY SHAFT; ORIGINAL CORNICE VISIBLE.
DEC_DETAIL: PEBBLE-FINISH WALL CLADDING; FULL-HEIGHT CONRETE WINDOW ENFRAMEMENTS ENHANCE VERTICALITY.
DES_RES: TWO-PART VERTICAL BLOCK; FIRST-STORY WINDOWS FILLED AND CENTER-BAY ENTRANCE IN SOUTH ELEVATION BLOCKED BY PLYWOOD.
CONTINUATION: THIS BUILDING APPEARS ON THE 1904 SANBORN MAP WITH THE NOTATION "FROM PLANS" AND STANDING ONLY FIVE STORIES. IN 1920, THE BUILDING WAS REMODELED AND TWO STORIES ADDED AT WHICH TIME IT WAS RENAMED THE WRIGHT BUILDING.  THE 1955 SANBORN MAP SHOWS THIS BUILDING AS THE "WRIGHT BLDG" CONTAINING SEVERAL STORES AND OFFICES.  THE CURRENT EXTERIOR APPEARANCE DATES TO A LATE 1960S REMODELING AND PREDATES THE MCGEE BUILDING COMPLEX.

DES_RES: SINGLE STORY CRAFTSMAN DUPLEX.  THE MAIN FRONT GABLE COVERS BOTH ENTRYWAYS.  ON THE EAST END OF THE FRONT FACADE ARE THREE STEPS, WHICH LEAD UP TO A PORCH.  THE MULTI-PANE DOOR IS FLANKED ON THE WEST SIDE BY TWO 5/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOWS WITH WIDE TRIM.  ON THE FRONT FACADE'S WEST END ARE ANOTHER THREE STEPS, WHICH LEAD UP TO A PORCH. THE ROOF IS SUPPORTED BY TWO TAPERED WOOD PIERS, WHICH ARE EACH BOLSTERED BY A BRICK PEDESTAL WITH CAPSTONE.  THE EAST ELEVATION FACES N BROADWAY.  ON THE EAST ELEVATION IS AN AWNING WINDOW AND A PAIR OF 5/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOWS WITH WIDE TRIM.  NORTH OF THESE WINDOWS IS A HIPPED WING, WHICH HAS ANOTHER PAIR OF 5/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOWS WITH WIDE TRIM ON THE EAST ELEVATION.  EAST AND WEST ELEVATIONS HAVE OPEN EAVES AND EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS.  FOUNDATION IS LOW BUT VISIBLE.

DES_RES: SINGLE STORY CRAFTSMAN WITH PERMASTONE SIDING.  ON THE FRONT FACADE'S EAST END IS THE BROAD ENTRY PORCH, WHICH HAS A FRONT-GABLED ROOF WITH WOOD FASCIA, THREE KNEE BRACES, OPEN EAVES, AND PERMASTONE INTO THE GABLE END. ON THE WEST ELEVATION ARE TWO AWNING WINDOWS SEPARATED BY AN EXTERIOR CHIMNEY.  NORTH OF THE WINDOWS IS A BOX WINDOW WITH A FRONT-GABLED ROOF AND THREE 4/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOWS.  NORTH OF THE BOX WINDOW IS A 5/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOW.

DOC_SOURCE: SANBORN 1922; SANBORN 1922-1955; OKLAHOMA COUNTY ASSESSOR
NAME_PREP: PETYA STEFANOFF; CARLOS MOORE; STEPHANIE BALLARD
EXTER_FEA: SINGLE STORY; FULL WIDTH PORCH
DEC_DETAIL: OPEN EAVES; EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS; TO-THE-GROUND PEDESTALS; TAPERED PIERS; CAPSTONES;
DES_RES: SINGLE STORY CRAFTSMAN WITH WOOD SIDING.  FOUR STEPS LEAD UP TO THE FULL-WIDTH PORCH.  THERE IS A LOW BRICK WALL WITH CAPSTONE ON THE EAST AND WEST SIDES OF THE STEPS AND A METAL RAILING ON THE WEST.  THE ORIGINAL PORCH HAS A FRONT-GABLED ROOF WITH OPEN EAVES, EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS, AND WOOD SIDING INTO THE GABLE END.  IT IS SUPPORTED BY TWO SQUARED TAPERED PIERS, EACH OF WHICH IS BOLSTERED BY A TO-THE-GROUND BRICK PEDESTAL.  EAST OF THE FRONT GABLE, AN ORIGINAL SIDE GABLE WITH OPEN EAVES AND EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS COVERS A SECOND, RECESSED ENTRYWAY.  THE ROOF HAS A SINGLE SQUARED POST SUPPORT.  A PORCH EXTENSION WEST OF THE ORIGINAL PORCH HAS A FOURTH BRICK PEDESTAL WITH A CAPSTONE.  A LOW RAILING PARTIALLY ENCLOSES THE ENTIRE PORCH AREA.  THE PANELED, MULTI-PANE DOOR IS FLANKED ON THE WEST SIDE BY A CENTRAL 1/1 PRAIRIE STYLE HUNG WOOD WINDOW WITH SMALLER 1/1 HUNG PRAIRIE STYLE WOOD FLANKERS.  EAST OF THE DOOR IS A LARGE 1/1 PRAIRIE STYLE WOOD WINDOW.  WINDOWS HAVE WIDE TRIM.  ON THE EAST ELEVATION ARE FOUR 1/1 HUNG PRAIRIE STYLE WOOD WINDOWS AND A BOX WINDOW, WHICH HAS A SHED ROOF WITH OPEN EAVES, EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS, AND THREE 1/1 HUNG PRAIRIE STYLE WOOD WINDOWS.

THE PORCH ROOF HAS OPEN EAVES, EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS, THREE KNEE BRACES AT THE GABLE END, AND IS SUPPORTED BY THREE METAL REPLACEMENT  SUPPORTS.  THE DOOR HAS MODEST ARCHITRAVE TRIM AND AN EARED LINTEL.  IT IS FLANKED ON THE EAST SIDE BY A 1/1 HUNG WOOD PRAIRIE STYLE WINDOW WITH EARNED LINTEL AND TRIM. EXTER_FEA: SINGLE STORY; FULL-WIDTH PORCH; WIDE EAVES; SYMMETRICAL FACADE
DEC_DETAIL: OPEN EAVES; EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS; TAPERED PIERS
DES_RES: SINGLE STORY CRAFTSMAN WITH WOOD SIDING.  A SET OF STEPS FLANKED ON EITHER SIDE BY A LOW BRICK WALL WITH CAPSTONE LEADS UP TO THE FULL-WIDTH PORCH.  THE PORCH IS COVERED BY THE MAIN FRONT GABLE, WHICH HAS WOOD SIDING, THREE EXPOSED RAFTERS, AND A RECTANGULAR AWNING WINDOW AT THE GABLE END.  THE ROOF ALSO HAS OPEN EAVES AND EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS AND IS SUPPORTED BY TWO LARGE BRICK PIERS THAT ARE INTEGRATED INTO A LOW BRICK WALL THAT PARTIALLY ENCLOSES THE PORCH.  THE TWO CENTRAL DOORS ARE BOARD AND BATTEN AND EACH HAS A SMALL RECTANGULAR WINDOW.  THE DOORS ARE SET BETWEEN TWO PAIRS OF 6/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOWS WITH MODEST TRIM.  THERE ARE TWO BOX WINDOWS WITH JERKINHEAD ROOFS ON THE EAST ELEVATION AND A BAY WINDOW ON THE WEST ELEVATION.  SECONDARY STRUCTURE NORTH OF BUILDING NOT VISIBLE FROM STREET.
COMMENTS: SINGLE DWELLING IN SANBORN 1922.  MULTIPLE DWELLING IN SANBORN 1922-1955.  ACCORDING TO SANBORNS FRONT PORCH APPEARS TO HAVE BEEN PARTIAL AND THEN EXPANDED TO FULL-WIDTH POST 1955

EXTER_FEA: SINGLE STORY; FULL WIDTH PORCH; WIDE EAVES
DEC_DETAIL: TAPERED PIERS; EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS; BRICK PIERS WITH CAPSTONES
DES_RES: SINGLE STORY CRAFTSMAN WITH WOOD SIDING.  TWO STEPS LEAD UP TO THE FULL-WIDTH ENTRY PORCH, WHICH IS COVERED BY THE MAIN HIPPED ROOF.  BELOW THE ROOF IS A WIDE FRIEZE, WHICH RESTS ON TWO TAPERED PIERS.  THE PIERS ARE BOLSTERED BY BRICK PIERS, WHICH HAVE CAPSTONES AND ARE INTEGRATED INTO A LOW BRICK WALL,  A THIRD BRICK PIER SITS BETWEEN THE PORCH SUPPORTS.  THERE ARE TWO DOORS, BOTH WITH 8 SMALL LITES.  WEST OF EACH DOOR IS A PAIR OF 6/1 HUNG WOODEN WINDOWS WITH MODEST TRIM AND ALUMINUM SCREENS.  ON THE WEST ELEVATION IS A SECONDARY ENTRYWAY, WHICH HAS A SHED ROOF, OPEN EAVES, EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS, TWO KNEE BRACES, DOOR, AND TWO HUNG WINDOWS.  ON THE NORTH AND SOUTH SIDES OF THE ENTRYWAY IS A 10/1 HUNG WINDOW.  SOUTHWEST OF MAIN BUILDING IS A GARAGE WITH A SINGLE-CAR BAY AND OVERHEAD DOOR.
COMMENTS: SINGLE DWELLING IN SANBORN 1922.  DUPLEX IN SANBORN 1922-1949.

DEC_DETAIL: OPEN EAVES; EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS; PRAIRIE STYLE WINDOWS; KNEE BRACES
DES_RES: SINGLE STORY CRAFTSMAN WITH WOOD SIDING.  VISIBLE FOUNDATION IS STUCCOED.  A SET OF FOUR STEPS WITH A METAL RAILING ON EITHER SIDE LEADS UP TO THE FULL-WIDTH PORCH.  THE MAIN FRONT GABLE COVERS THE PORCH AND HAS WOOD SIDING AND THREE KNEE BRACES AT THE GABLE END, OPEN EAVES, AND EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS.  THE ORIGINAL PORCH SUPPORTS HAVE BEEN REPLACED BY FOUR METAL SUPPORTS WITH BRACKETS.  THE SLAB DOOR HAS A RECTANGULAR WINDOW AND IS FLANKED ON THE WEST SIDE BY A 1/1 HUNG PRAIRIE-STYLE WOOD WINDOW WITH 1/1 HUNG PRAIRIE-STYLE WOOD FLANKERS.  EAST OF THE DOOR IS A LARGE 1/1 HUNG PRAIRIE-STYLE WOOD WINDOW AND ANOTHER, RECESSED ENTRYWAY WITH A SLAB DOOR UNDER A SIDE GABLE.  WEST ELEVATION HAS TWO WOOD AWNING WINDOWS SEPARATED BY AN EXTERIOR CHIMNEY, AND A BOX WINDOW WITH A ROW OF THREE HUNG WOOD WINDOWS.
COMMENTS: IN 1922 SANBORN BUILDING WAS A SINGLE DWELLING WITH THE ADDRESS 114 NW 20TH ST.  BUILDING BECAME A DUPLEX IN OR BEFORE 1949 (SANBORN 1922-1949) WITH THE ADDRESS 112-114 NW 20TH ST.  VERIFY DATE OF EXTANT PORCH SUPPORTS.

DEC_DETAIL: GABLE RETURNS; TAPERED WOOD PIERS; BRICK PEDESTALS
DES_RES: SINGLE STORY CRAFTSMAN WITH ASBESTOS SIDING AND CLOSED EAVES.  A SET OF FOUR STEPS FLANKED ON EITHER SIDE BY A SHORT BRICK PIER WITH A CAPSTONE LEADS UP TO THE BROAD ENTRY PORCH.  A FRONT GABLE COVERS THE PORCH AND HAS GABLE RETURNS AND ASBESTOS SIDING AND A RECTANGULAR VENT AT THE GABLE END.  THE ROOF IS SUPPORTED BY TWO TAPERED WOOD PIERS, EACH OF WHICH IS SUPPORTED BY A TO-THE-GROUND BRICK PEDESTAL THAT HAS BEEN PAINTED WHITE WITH A CAPSTONE.  A LOW BRICK WALL THAT HAS BEEN PAINTED WHITE PARTIALLY ENCLOSES THE PORCH.  THE SLAB DOOR HAS A MODEST ARCHITRAVE TRIM AND SIMULATED CROSSHEAD PEDIMENT.  EAST OF THE DOOR IS A 5/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOW WITH MODEST TRIM.  EAST OF THE PORCH IS ANOTHER 5/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOW WITH MODEST TRIM.  WEST ELEVATION HAS A MULTI-PANE AWNING WINDOW AND THREE HUNG WINDOWS, ALL WITH MODEST TRIM.
COMMENTS: ASSESSOR AND SANBORN STATE ADDRESS AS 115 NW 22ND.  VERIFY DATE OF ASBESTOS APPLICATION.

DES_RES: SINGLE STORY CRAFTSMAN WITH WOOD SIDING.  A SET OF STEPS WITH IRON RAILINGS LEADS UP TO THE PARTIAL PORCH.  A FRONT GABLE COVERS THE PORCH AND HAS WOOD INTO THE GABLE END, THREE KNEE BRACES, AND IS SUPPORTED BY TWO TAPERED WOOD PIERS.  EACH PIER IS BOLSTERED BY A TO-THE-GROUND BRICK PEDESTAL WITH A CAPSTONE.  A LOW BRICK WALL PARTIALLY ENCLOSES THE PORCH.  A THIRD BRICK PEDESTAL WITHOUT A PIER STANDS ON THE EAST SIDE OF THE STEPS.  THE DOOR IS FLANKED ON THE EAST SIDE BY A PAIR OF 1/1 HUNG WOOD COTTAGE WINDOWS.  WEST OF THE PORCH IS A FIXED COTTAGE WINDOW AND ANOTHER 1/1 HUNG COTTAGE WINDOW.  EAST ELEVATION HAS FOUR 1/1 HUNG COTTAGE WINDOWS.  SOUTH OF THE BUILDING IS A FRONT-GABLED GARAGE WITH TWO SINGLE CAR BAYS THAT IS SHARED WITH 110 NW 21ST.

DES_RES: TWO-AND-ONE-HALF STORY COLONIAL REVIVAL HOUSE. FIRST FLOOR HAS A PORCH WITH BRICK COLUMNS AND WOOD BALUSTERS. THE PORCH HAS A PEDIMENT GABLE WITH AN UNORNAMENTED FREIZE. THE MAIN WINDOWS ON THE FACADE HAVE MULTI-LIGHT UPPER SASHES AND A SINGLE LOWER SASH. SMALLER WINDOWS ARE FOUR-OVER-ONE THAT ARE SEPARATED BY TAPERED COLUMNS. THE ENTRY DOOR ON THE FIRST FLOOR HAS SINGLE PANE SIDELIGHTS. THE GABLE FRONT ROOF HAS OPEN EAVES WITH GABLE RETURNS. THE WEST ELEVATION HAS A TWO-STORY BOX WINDOW. THE EAST ELEVATION HAS NO ORNAMENTATION.

EXTER_FEA: SINGLE STORY; BROAD ENTRY PORCH
DEC_DETAIL: EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS; FIRIEZE BOARD; BRICK PIERS WITH CAPSTONES
DES_RES: SINGLE STORY CRAFTSMAN WITH WOOD SIDING.  TWO CONCRETE STEPS LEAD UP TO A BROAD ENTRY PORCH ON THE FRONT FACADE'S EAST SIDE.  THE PORCH IS COVERED BY A SIDE GABLE, WHICH HAS EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS AT THE GABLE END,.  TWO LARGE BRICK PIERS SUPPORT THE ROOF UNDER A WIDE FRIEZE BOARD.  BOTH PIERS HAVE CAPSTONES.  THE PIERS CONNECT TO A LOW STONE WALL AND A THIRD, SHORTER PIER IS SET BETWEEN TO THE LOAD-BEARING PIERS.  THE DOOR HAS THREE RECTANGULAR WINDOWS AND IS ON THE PORCH'S WEST END.  EAST OF THE DOOR IS A PAIR OF 9/1 HUNG WINDOWS WITH TRIM AND A MODEST CORNICE.  THE MAIN FRONT GABLE CAN BE SEEN ATOP THE PORCH SIDE GABLE.  WEST OF THE PORCH IS A ROW OF THREE 9/1 HUNG WINDOWS WITH TRIM AND MODEST CORNICE.  THERE ARE TWO FRONT-GABLED, TO-THE-GROUND BAY WINDOWS ON THE EAST ELEVATION.  SIDE-GABLED SECONDARY STRUCTURE NOT OF BUILDING.

EXTER_FEA: SINGLE STORY; FULL-WIDTH PORCH
DEC_DETAIL: METAL PORCH SUPPORTS; WIDE CLOSED EAVES
DES_RES: SINGLE STORY BUNGALOW/CRAFTSMAN WITH VINYL SIDING.  A SET OF THREE STAIRS BOUNDED BY RAILINGS ON EITHER SIDE LEADS UP TO THE FULL-WIDTH PORCH.  A SIDE GABLE COVERS THE PORCH.  THE ORIGINAL PORCH SUPPORTS HAVE BEEN REPLACED BY FOUR METAL SUPPORTS, EACH WITH BRACKETS.  A METAL RAILING PARTIALLY ENCLOSES THE PORCH.  THE WOOD DOOR HAS FOUR RECTANGULAR PANES.  EAST OF THE DOOR IS A LARGE 9/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOW.  WEST OF THE DOOR IS A 6/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOW WITH 4/1 HUNG WOOD FLANKERS.  BELOW THE WINDOWS THE VINYL SIDING GIVES WAY TO STONE.  THE MAIN FRONT GABLE IS VISIBLE ATOP THE PORCH ROOF.  EXTERIOR CHIMNEY AND BOX WINDOW ON WEST ELEVATION.
COMMENTS: REPLACEMENT PORCH SUPPORTS AND SIDING.

NAME_PREP: VIREAK THEY; COLLIN POWER; STEPHANIE BALLARD
EXTER_FEA: SINGLE STORY; FULL-WIDTH PORCH
DEC_DETAIL: OPEN EAVES; EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS; TAPERED PIERS; BRICK PEDESTALS; CAPSTONES
DES_RES: SINGLE STORY CRAFTSMAN WITH WOOD SIDING.  A LOW BRICK PIER WITH A CAPSTONE FLANKS THE TWO STEPS THAT LEAD UP TO THE FULL-WIDTH PORCH ON EITHER SIDE.  A SIDE GABLE WITH OPEN EAVES AND EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS COVERS THE PORCH.  THE ROOF IS SUPPORTED BY THREE TAPERED WOOD PIERS, WHICH ARE BOLSTERED BY BRICK PEDESTALS.  A SHORT, CENTERED ROWLOCK COURSE RUNS ALONG THE TOP OF EACH PEDESTAL.  A LOW WOOD RAILING PARTIALLY ENCLOSES THE PORCH.  THE SLAB DOOR HAS WOOD ARCHITRAVE TRIM AND IS FLANKED ON THE WEST SIDE BY A 6/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOW WITH 4/1 HUNG WOOD FLANKERS.  ALL THREE WINDOWS HAVE ALUMINUM SCREENS.  EAST OF THE DOOR IS A LARGE 8/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOW.  EAST ELEVATION HAS A DOUBLE HUNG WOOD WINDOW AND TWO GABLED PROJECTIONS, EACH WITH TWO DOUBLE HUNG WOOD WINDOWS.  ALL OF THE WINDOWS HAVE WOOD TRIM, LINTELS, AND SILLS.

DES_RES: SINGLE STORY CRAFTSMAN WITH WOOD SIDING.  A SET OF STEPS LEADS UP TO THE BROAD PORCH.  A SIDE GABLED ROOF WITH OPEN EAVES AND EXPOSED RAFTER HEADS COVERS THE PORCH AND IS SUPPORTED BY TWO TAPERED WOOD PIERS.  EACH PIER IS BOLSTERED BY A BRICK PEDESTAL WITH A CAPSTONE.  THE SLAB DOOR HAS MODEST ARCHITRAVE TRIM AND EARED LINTEL.  WEST OF THE DOOR IS A 6/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOW WITH WIDE TRIM, CONTINUOUS EARED LINTEL, AND TWO 3/1 HUNG WOOD FLANKERS.  EAST OF THE PORCH IS A FRONT-GABLED WING, WHICH HAS A ROW OF THREE 1/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOWS WITH MODEST TRIM AND EARED LINTEL.  THE MAIN FRONT GABLE IS VISIBLE ATOP THE PORCH ROOF.  FRONT-GABLED GARAGE NORTH OF BUILDING WITH SINGLE CAR BAY.

DEC_DETAIL: BRICK PIERS; OPEN EAVES; EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS; CAPSTONE' ROWLOCK COURSE
DES_RES: SINGLE STORY CRAFTSMAN.  LOWER SECTION OF THE BUILDING HAS REPLACEMENT PERMASTONE.  UPPER PORTION HAS REPLACEMENT VINYL SIDING.  A FLAT-ROOFED PORCH ADDITION PROVIDES ENTRANCE TO THE PORCH ON THE WEST END OF THE FRONT FACADE.  THE ROOF HAS OPEN EAVES AND IS SUPPORTED BY A METAL SUPPORT, WHICH HIS BOLSTERED BY A BRICK PEDESTAL WITH A CAPSTONE.  EAST OF THE ADDITION IS THE ORIGINAL PORCH, WHICH HAS A FRONT-GABLED ROOF WITH TWO VENTS, VINYL SIDING, AND THREE KNEE BRACES AT THE GABLE END.  THE ROOF IS SUPPORTED BY TWO LARGE BRICK PIERS.  THERE IS A METAL AWNING OFF THE GABLE END.  THE DOOR IS FLANKED ON THE EAST AND WEST SIDES BY WINDOWS, WHICH ARE INDISCERNIBLE DUE TO DARK SCREENS.  EAST OF THE ORIGINAL PORCH IS AN OPEN PORCH EXTENSION WITH A SINGLE BRICK PIER THAT HAS A CAPSTONE.  WEST ELEVATION HAS AN EXTERNAL CHIMNEY, A BOX WINDOW WITH THREE 4/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOWS AND A GABLE ROOF, AND A SEPARATE 5/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOW.
COMMENTS: REPLACEMENT VINYL AND PERMASTONE SIDING; EAST AND WEST EXTENSIONS OF PORCH

A WOOD RAILING ENCLOSES THE SECOND FLOOR PORCH.

EXTER_FEA: SINGLE STORY; FULL-WIDTH PORCH; SYMMETRICAL FACADE
DEC_DETAIL: OPEN EAVES; EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS; TAPERED PIERS; BRICK PEDESTALS
DES_RES: SINGLE STORY CRAFTSMAN WITH WOOD SIDING.  A SET OF STAIRS FLANKED ON EITHER SIDE BY A BRICK WALL WITH CAPSTONE LEADS UP TO THE FULL-WIDTH PORCH.  THE FRONT-GABLED ROOF HAS A RECTANGULAR VENT, EXPOSED RAFTERS, AND WOOD SIDING AT THE GABLE END AS WELL AS OPEN EAVES AND EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS.  THE ROOF IS SUPPORTED BY FOUR TAPERED PIERS, WHICH REST UPON BRICK PEDESTALS.  THE PEDESTALS ARE INTEGRATED INTO A BRICK WALL, WHICH PARTIALLY ENCLOSES THE PORCH AND HAS TWO TRIANGULAR, DECORATIVE OPENINGS WITH BRICK ROWLOCK BORDER.  THE WALL IS TOPPED BY A BRICK ROWLOCK COURSE.  THE CENTRAL SLAB DOOR HAS A CORNICE AND ARCHITRAVE TRIM.  EAST AND WEST OF THE DOOR IS A 6/1 HUNG WINDOW WITH 4/1 HUNG FLANKERS, TRIM, AND A MODEST CORNICE.  EAST AND WEST ELEVATIONS HAVE A BOX WINDOW WITH A GABLED ROOF.  APPARENTLY SHARED GARAGE WITH 126 NW 19TH SOUTHWEST OF BUILDING.

EXTER_FEA: SINGLE STORY; BROAD ENTRY PORCH
DEC_DETAIL: OPEN EAVES; EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS; BRICK PIERS; CAPSTONES; SPINDLEWORK FRIEZE; MODEST WINDOW TRIM
DES_RES: SINGLE STORY CRAFTSMAN WITH WOOD SIDING.  THE BROAD ENTRY PORCH ON THE EAST END OF THE FRONT FACADE IS COVERED BY A FRONT-GABLED ROOF, WHICH HAS WOOD SIDING INTO THE GABLE END, OPEN EAVES, EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS, AND A SPINDLEWORK FRIEZE.  THE ROOF IS SUPPORTED BY TWO LARGE BRICK PIERS, EACH WITH A CAPSTONE.  THERE APPEAR TO BE TWO SEPARATE DOORS.  EAST OF THE DOORS IS A PAIR OF 4/1 DOUBLE HUNG WOOD WINDOWS WITH ALUMINUM SCREENS.  WEST OF THE DOORS IS A 6/1 DOUBLE HUNG WOOD WINDOW WITH 4/1 DOUBLE HUNG WOOD FLANKERS, ALL WITH ALUMINUM SCREENS AND MODEST TRIM.  THE MAIN FRONT GABLE IS VISIBLE BEHIND AND TO THE WEST OF THE PORCH.  WEST ELEVATION HAS TWO AWNING WINDOWS SEPARATED BY AN EXTERIOR BRICK CHIMNEY, A BOX WINDOW WITH A GABLED ROOF AND THREE DOUBLE HUNG WINDOWS, AND A SEPARATE DOUBLE HUNG WINDOW.
COMMENTS: SANBORNS 1922-1955 INDICATE FULL-WIDTH PORCH AS OPPOSED TO EXTANT PARTIAL WIDTH PORCH.

DEC_DETAIL: OPEN EAVES; EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS; TAPERED WOOD PIERS; BRICK PEDESTALS; CAPSTONES
DES_RES: SINGLE STORY CRAFTSMAN.  A SET OF FOUR STEPS FLANKED ON THE EAST AND WEST SIDES BY A SHORT BRICK PIER WITH A RUSTICATED CAPSTONE LEADS UP TO THE FULL-WIDTH PORCH.  A FRONT GABLE WITH THREE KNEE BRACES, A VENT, AND ASBESTOS SIDING AT THE GABLE END COVERS THE PORCH ON THE EAST END. A SIDE GABLE COVERS THE PORCH ON THE WEST END.  THE PORCH ROOF HAS OPEN EAVES, EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS, AND IS SUPPORTED BY FOUR TAPERED WOOD PIERS.  EACH OF THE PIERS IS BOLSTERED BY A PAINTED BRICK PEDESTAL WITH A RUSTICATED CAPSTONE.  THE MULTI-PANE DOOR IS FLANKED ON THE EAST SIDE BY A PAIR OF 5/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOWS.  WEST OF THE DOOR IS A 5/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOW WITH TWO 3/1 HUNG WOOD FLANKERS.  WINDOW TRIM IS THINNER THAN ORIGINAL.  A WOOD RAILING PARTIALLY ENCLOSES THE PORCH.  THE UPPER PART OF THE BUILDING HAS ASBESTOS SIDING.  THE LOWER PARS IS STONE.  ON THE EAST ELEVATION ARE TWO 4/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOWS SEPARATED BY A GABLED SECTION THAT HAS TWO 4/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOWS AND AN AWNING WINDOW.

DES_RES: SINGLE STORY CRAFTSMAN WITH WOOD SIDING AND SYMMETRICAL FACADE.  THE FRONT-GABLED ROOF HAS A KNEE BRACE AT THE APEX, WOOD SIDING AT THE GABLE END, AND EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS.  A SHED ROOF WITH TWO KNEE BRACES COVERS A RECTANGULAR WINDOW AT THE GABLE END.  THE MAIN FRONT GABLE IS SUPPORTED BY THREE WOODEN TAPERED PIERS, WHICH ARE BOLSTERED BY BRICK PIERS WITH CAPSTONES.  TWO OTHER BRICK PIERS, EACH WITH A CAPSTONE, IS SET BETWEEN THE ROOF SUPPORTS AND ARE INTEGRATED INTO A LOW RAILING THAT PARTIALLY ENCLOSES THE PORCH.  TWO 1/1 HUNG WINDOWS SEPARATE THE TWO DOORS, WHICH ARE ON THE EAST AND WEST ENDS OF THE FRONT FACADE, RESPECTIVELY.  THE EAST DOOR IS SLAB WITH TWO WINDOWS.  THE WEST DOOR HAS DIVIDED LITES.  THERE IS A SIDE-GABLED WING ON THE SOUTH ELEVATION

CONTINUATION: THIS BUILDING APPEARS ON THE 1922 SANBORN FIRE INSURANCE MAP AS CONTAINING A WHOLESALE AUTO TIRE SHOP.  THE 1928 CITY DIRECTORY LISTS FIRESTONE TIRES HERE. THE 1950 AND 1955 SANBORN MAPS SHOW THIS BUILDING CONTAINING A PRINTING SHOP ON THE 2ND AND 3RD FLOORS AND A STORE ON THE 1ST FLOOR. A RESTAURANT OCCUPIED THE EAST HALF OF THE FIRST FLOOR IN 1950.

NAME_PREP: RYAN CONNER; MITCHELL MOORE; STEPHANIE BALLARD
EXTER_FEA: SINGLE STORY; ENTRY PORCH; WIDE EAVES; VISIBLE FOUNDATION
DEC_DETAIL: TAPERED WOODEN PIER ON BRICK PEDESTAL; CAPSTONES; KNEE BRACES
DES_RES: SINGLE STORY CRAFTSMAN BUNGALOW WITH VINYL SIDING.  A SET OF STEPS FLANKED ON THE EAST AND WEST SIDES BY A LOW BRICK WALL WITH CAPSTONE LEADS UP TO THE ENTRY PORCH.  A FRONT GABLE WITH THREE KNEE BRACES COVERS THE PORCH.  THE ROOF IS SUPPORTED BY ONE TAPERED WOODEN PIER, WHICH IS BOLSTERED BY A BRICK PEDESTAL WITH A CAPSTONE.  THE SLAB DOOR HAS THREE RECTANGULAR PANES AND IS RECESSED.  EAST OF THE DOOR IS A 5/1 HUNG WINDOW.  WEST OF THE ENTRY PORCH IS THE ORIGINAL PORCH, WHICH HAS BEEN ENCLOSED.  THIS SECTION NOW HAS A ROW OF THREE 6/6 HUNG WINDOWS ON THE FRONT FACADE AND A ROW OF FOUR 6/6 HUNG WINDOWS ON THE WEST ELEVATION. THE BRICK FOUNDATION IS VISIBLE.  EAST OF THE ENTRYWAY IS A HUNG WINDOW UNDER THE MAIN FRONT GABLE, WHICH HAS BEEN EXTENDED TO COVER AN OPEN PORCH ADDITION ON THE EAST ELEVATION.  EXTERNAL CHIMNEY ON WEST ELEVATION.  FRONT-GABLED SECONDARY STRUCTURE NORTH OF BUILDING.
COMMENTS: SINGLE DWELLING IN SANBORN 1922.  DUPLEX IN SANBORNS 1922-1949, 1922-1950, 1922-1955.  EAST ELEVATION PORCH ADDED BETWEEN 1922-1949.  FRONT FACADE PORCH ENCLOSED AFTER 1955.

ON THE EAST END IS A SIDE GABLE, WHICH WRAPS AROUND TO THE EAST ELEVATION.  THE ROOF IS SUPPORTED BY FOUR TAPERED WOOD PIERS, EACH OF WHICH IS BOLSTERED BY A BRICK PEDESTAL WITH CAPSTONE.  A LOW WOOD RAILING PARTIALLY ENCLOSES THE PORCH.  A FIFTH PEDESTAL WITH A CAPSTONE AND WITHOUT A PIER STANDS TO THE WEST OF THE PORCH ENTRYWAY.  THE MULTI-PANE DOOR IS FLANKED ON THE WEST SIDE BY A LARGE 8/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOW WITH TWO 5/1 HUNG FLANKERS, WIDE TRIM, AND AN EARED LINTEL.  EAST OF THE DOOR IS A ROW OF FOUR PRAIRIE-STYLE FIXED WINDOWS WITH WIDE TRIM AND AN EARED LINTEL.  THE MAIN FRONT GABLE IS VISIBLE ATOP THE SIDE-GABLED PORCH ROOF.
COMMENTS: SINGLE DWELLING IN SANBORN 1922.  DUPLEX IN SANBORNS 1922-1949, 1922-1950, AND 1922-1955

DES_RES: TWO STORY STUCCOED CRAFTSMAN.  THREE STEPS FLANKED ON EITHER SIDE BY A LOW PIER WITH CAPSTONE LEAD UP TO THE ORIGINAL BROAD PORCH.  THE ORIGINAL PORCH HAS A FRONT-GABLED ROOF WITH OPEN EAVES AND EXPOSED RAFTERS.  THE ROOF IS SUPPORTED BY TWO STUCCOED PIERS.  THE DOOR IS FLANKED ON THE WEST SIDE BY A 24/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOW.  THE PORCH HAS BEEN EXTENDED WEST IN FRONT OF A AN ORIGINAL FRONT-GABLED SECTION THAT HAS AN 24/1 HUNG WINDOW.  THE PORCH ADDITION HAS TWO MORE SHORT PIERS, EACH WITH A CAPSTONE.  EAST OF THE PORCH IS A PORTE COCHERE ADDITION WITH TWO SQUARED PIERS, EACH WITH A CAPSTONE, AND A TRELLIS ROOF.  ON THE SECOND STORY IS A FRONT-GABLED WING WITH OPEN EAVES, EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS, AND TWO 15/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOWS.  FLANKING THIS SECTION ON EITHER SIDE IS A SIDE-GABLED WING, WHICH HAS OPEN EAVES, EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS, AND A PAIR OF 15/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOWS.

A LARGE FRONT GABLE WITH WOOD SIDING AT THE GABLE END, WIDE FRIEZE BOARD, OPEN EAVES, AND EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS COVERS THE PORCH.  THE ROOF IS SUPPORTED BY TWO GROUPS OF THREE SQUARED WOOD POSTS, WHICH ARE BOLSTERED BY STONE PIERS WITH CAPSTONES.  THE PIERS ARE INTEGRATED INTO A LOW STONE WALL THAT PARTIALLY ENCLOSES THE PORCH.  THE CENTRAL DOOR HAS A MODEST CORNICE AND ARCHITRAVE TRIM.  WEST OF THE DOOR IS A ROW OF THREE 4/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOWS WITH MODEST CORNICE AND TRIM.  EAST OF THE DOOR ARE TWO 4/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOWS WITH MODEST CORNICE AND TRIM.  THE THIRD, MIDDLE WINDOW HAS BEEN CONVERTED INTO A DOOR.

STEPS LEAD UP TO THE FULL-WIDTH PORCH, WHICH IS COVERED BY A FRONT GABLE WITH WOOD SIDING AT THE GABLE END, FIVE KNEE BRACES, A FASCIA WITH DIAMOND MOTIFS, AND A WIDE FRIEZE WITH AN ART DECO MOTIF. A LOW BRICK WALL TOPPED BY A BRICK ROWLOCK COURSE PARTIALLY ENCLOSES THE PORCH.  THE PANELED DOOR HAS MODEST ARCHITRAVE TRIM AND LINTEL.  FLANKING THE DOOR ON EITHER SIDE IS A PAIR OF 10/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOWS, EACH WITH AN ALUMINUM SCREEN.  ON THE 1 1/2 STORY ARE TWO 8/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOWS SEPARATED BY A ROW OF THREE 8/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOWS.  ALL WINDOWS HAVE MODEST TRIM AND LINTELS.  1 1/2 STORY HAS A HIPPED ROOF WITH OPEN EAVES AND EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS.  EXTERNAL CHIMNEY ON WEST ELEVATION.
COMMENTS: VERIFY DATE OF SECOND FLOOR ADDITION - FIRST PRESENT ON SANBORN 1922-1949

DEC_DETAIL: OPEN EAVES; EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS; WOOD PIERS; BRICK PEDESTALS; CAPSTONES; STICKWORK
DES_RES: SINGLE STORY CRAFTSMAN WITH WOOD SIDING.  A SET OF STEPS ON THE WEST ELEVATION LEADS UP TO THE BROAD PORCH.  ON THE FRONT FACADE (NORTH ELEVATION) A FRONT GABLED ROOF WITH EXPOSED FALSE BEAMS, OPEN EAVES, EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS AND STICKWORK AT THE OPEN GABLE END COVERS THE PORCH.  THE ROOF IS SUPPORTED BY TWO SQUARED PIERS, WHICH REST UPON TWO BRICK PEDESTALS, EACH WITH A CAPSTONE.  A WOOD RAILING PARTIALLY ENCLOSES THE PORCH.  THE DOOR IS IS ON THE WEST END OF THE PORCH.  EAST OF THE DOOR IS A ROW OF THREE 4/1 COTTAGE WINDOWS WITH WIDE TRIM AND CORNICE.  WEST OF THE PORCH IS ANOTHER ROW OF THREE 4/1 COTTAGE WINDOWS WITH WIDE TRIM AND CORNICE.  PORCH HAS A RAISED FOUNDATION.  THERE IS AN EXTERIOR CHIMNEY ON THE EAST ELEVATION.

desc_seg: WARRANTS FURTHER STUDY AS A CONTRIBUTING RESOURCE IN THE HERITAGE HILLS EAST HISTORIC DISTRICT
DOC_SOURCE: SANBORN 1922; SANBORN 1922-1955
NAME_PREP: NOLAN APARICIO; GRACE SANDERS; LYNDA OZAN
EXTER_FEA: TWO ENTRIES; BRICK WATER TABLE
DEC_DETAIL: BRICK SOLDIER COURSE; BRICK PARAPET
DES_RES: THIS E-SHAPED BUILDING IS SIX BAYS WIDE, CLAD WITH BRICK AND HAS TWO EVENLY SPACED ENTRIES. THE FIRST AND SIXTH BAYS ARE IDENTICAL: EACH HAS THREE FOUR-OVER-ONE HUNG WINDOWS ON ALL THREE FLOORS. EACH WINDOW  HAS A BRICK SILL AND A SOLDIER COURSE LINTEL WITH STONE DETAILS. BAYS TWO AND FIVE ARE IDENTICAL AND ALIGN WITH AN INTERIOR STAIRCASE: THE FIRST FLOOR HAS A PANE ENTRY DOOR WITH MULTI-LIGHT SIDELIGHTS; ON EITHER SIDE OF THE ENTRY AREA IS A FOUR-OVER-ONE HUNG WINDOW; ABOVE THE ENTRY ARE TWO LARGER FOUR-OVER-ONE HUNG WINDOWS; ALIGNED WITH THE SECOND FLOOR ARE TWO SMALLER FOUR-OVER-ONE HUNG WINDOWS; AT THE LANDING ARE TWO LARGER FOUR-OVER-ONE HUNG WINDOWS; ALIGNED WITH THE THIRD FLOOR ARE TWO SMALLER FOUR-OVER-ONE HUNG WINDOWS. BAYS THREE AND FOUR ARE IDENTICAL: EACH HAS THREE FOUR-OVER-ONE HUNG WINDOWS ON ALL THREE FLOORS. EACH WINDOW  HAS A BRICK SILL AND A SOLDIER COURSE LINTEL WITH STONE DETAILS. THE PARAPET IS STEPPED AND HAS DECORATIVE BANDS OF SOLDIER COURSE BRICK. THE EAST ELEVATION IS TWO BAYS WIDE. EACH BAY HAS EACH HAS THREE FOUR-OVER-ONE HUNG WINDOWS ON ALL THREE FLOORS. EACH WINDOW  HAS A BRICK SILL AND A SOLDIER COURSE LINTEL WITH STONE DETAILS EXCEPT FOR THE THIRD FLOOR WINDOWS. THE REAR, NORTH, ELEVATION ARE THE 'LEGS' OF THE E SHAPE. THE EAST AND WEST ELEVATIONS OF THE TOP AND BOTTOM OF THE 'E' EACH HAVE TWO FOUR-OVER-ONE HUNG WINDOWS ON ALL FLOORS. THE NORTH ELEVATION OF THESE SAME SECTIONS HAVE FOUR, FOUR-OVER-ONE HUNG WINDOWS. THESE SECTIONS ARE CLAD WITH WOOD CLAPBOARDS AND HAVE BRICK COLUMNS AT THE CORNERS. THE CORNERS OF EACH HAS A ROUND GLOBE AT THE PARAPET. THE CENTER LEG OF THE 'E' IS A THREE STORY SHED ROOF PORCH STRUCTURE WITH A STAIRCASE BETWEEN EACH LANDING.

DES_RES: TWO STORY CRAFTSMAN WITH WOOD SIDING.  THREE STEPS  LEAD UP TO THE FULL-WIDTH PORCH.  A FRONT GABLE COVERS THE EAST END OF THE PORCH AND A SIDE GABLE COVERS THE WEST.  THE FRONT GABLE HAS WOOD SIDING AT THE GABLE END AND THREE KNEE BRACES.  FIVE BRICK PIERS, EACH WITH A CAPSTONE, SUPPORT THE ROOF AND ARE INTEGRATED INTO A LOW BRICK WALL THAT PARTIALLY COVERS THE PORCH.  THE WALL IS TOPPED BY A ROWLOCK COURSE. WEST OF THE DOOR IS A LARGE 8/1 HUNG COTTAGE WOOD WINDOW WITH TWO 4/1 HUNG WOOD COTTAGE WINDOW FLANKERS, ALL WITH WIDE FRAMES.  PORCH WRAPS AROUND TO THE WEST ELEVATION. EXTER_FEA: 1 1/2 STORY; ENCLOSED PORCH; TWO ENTRYWAYS
DEC_DETAIL: OPEN EAVES; EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS; STONE PLANTER; KNEE BRACES; GLASS BLOCK SIDELIGHTS
DES_RES: 1 1/2 STORY CRAFTSMAN.  THREE STEPS LEAD UP TO THE STONE ENTRYWAY, WHICH IS ON THE NORTHWEST CORNER OF THE BUILDING.  THE DOOR IS FLANKED ON EITHER SIDE BY A GLASS BLOCK SIDELIGHT.  NORTH ELEVATION IS THE ORIGINAL FRONT FACADE.  THE ORIGINAL PORCH HAS BEEN COMPLETELY ENCLOSED.  A FRONT GABLE WITH WOOD SIDING AT THE GABLE END AND TWO KNEE BRACES COVERS THE WEST END OF THE ENCLOSED PORCH AND A SIDE GABLE COVERS THE EAST END.  THREE LARGE STONE PIERS ARE SEPARATED BY THREE PICTURE WINDOWS.  A STONE PLANTER RUNS IN FRONT OF THE FRONT FACADE.  EAST OF THE ORIGINAL BUILDING IS AN ATTACHED SHED-ROOFED SINGLE-CAR GARAGE WITH METAL SIDING.  ON THE 1 1/2 STORY OF THE FRONT FACADE ARE TWO WINDOWS SEPARATED BY A ROW OF FOUR WINDOWS.  SASHES ARE OBSCURED BY SHUTTERS.  THE BUILDING'S WEST ELEVATION FACES N ROBINSON.  ON THE FIRST STORY THERE IS A PICTURE WINDOW AND AN EXTERIOR CHIMNEY.  A STONE PLANTER RUNS BELOW THE WINDOW AND IN FRONT OF THE CHIMNEY.  SOUTH OF THE CHIMNEY IS ANOTHER ENTRYWAY, WHICH HAS A SLAB DOOR WITH THREE RECTANGULAR WINDOWS AND A METAL AWNING ROOF.  SOUTH OF THE ENTRYWAY IS A BOX PICTURE WINDOW.  ON THE WEST ELEVATION, 1 1/2 STORY ARE TWO WINDOWS, BOTH OBSCURED BY SHUTTERS, SEPARATED BY THE BRICK CHIMNEY STACK.  SECONDARY STRUCTURE SOUTH OF BUILDING.
COMMENTS: OFFICE IN SANBORN 1922-1955

EXTER_FEA: SINGLE STORY; FULL-WIDTH PORCH
DEC_DETAIL: EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS; BRICK WALL WITH CAPSTONE; TAPERED WOOD PIERS; BRICK PIERS WITH CAPSTONES
DES_RES: SINGLE STORY BRICK CRAFTSMAN.  TWO STEPS LEAD UP TO THE FULL-WIDTH PORCH.  THE WEST END THE PORCH HAS A FRONT-GABLED ROOF, WHICH CONNECTS TO A SIDE GABLE THAT COVERS THE PORCH ON THE EAST END.  THE MAIN FRONT GABLE IS VISIBLE ABOVE THE PORCH SIDE GABLE.  THE PORCH ROOF IS SUPPORTED BY THREE TAPERED WOODEN PIERS, EACH BOLSTERED BY A BRICK PIER WITH A CAPSTONE.  A FOURTH BRICK PIER WITH CAPSTONE FLANKS THE STAIRS ON THE WEST SIDE AND CONNECTS TO THE OTHERS VIA A BRICK WALL THAT PARTIALLY ENCLOSES THE PORCH.  PORCH ROOF HAS EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS AND VERTICAL WOOD SIDING AT THE GABLE END.  ON THE EAST AND WEST SIDES OF THE DOOR IS A LARGE 1/1 HUNG WINDOW WITH 1/1 HUNG FLANKERS.  MULTIPLE WINGS ON EAST AND WEST ELEVATIONS WITH GABLED ROOFS AND EXPOSED RAFTER TAILS.  HIPPED-ROOFED GARAGE WITH BAY AND OVERHEAD DOOR NORTH OF BUILDING, PARTIALLY VISIBLE FROM STREET.

NAME_PREP: VIREAK THEY; COLLIN POWER; STEPHANIE BALLARD
EXTER_FEA: TWO STORIES; FULL-WIDTH PORCH
DEC_DETAIL: TAPERED PIERS;  BRICK PEDESTALS; BRICK SOLDIER COURSE; BRICK ROWLOCK COURSE; KNEE BRACES; GABLE RETURNS
DES_RES: TWO STORY NEW TRADITIONAL CRAFTSMAN.  THE BRICK FIRST STORY HAS A FULL-WIDTH PORCH UNDER A HIPPED ROOF.  A FRONT GABLE COVERS THE PORCH ON THE WEST END AND HAS GABLE RETURNS AND A KNEE BRACE AT THE APEX.  THE ROOF IS SUPPORTED BY THREE TAPERED PIERS, EACH OF WHICH IS BOLSTERED BY A BRICK PEDESTAL WITH A ROWLOCK CAP.  THE PEDESTALS ARE CONNECTED BY A LOW BRICK WALL THAT PARTIALLY ENCLOSES THE PORCH AND IS TOPPED BY A BRICK ROWLOCK COURSE.  THE PANELED DOOR HAS THREE SMALL, RECTANGULAR WINDOWS.  EAST OF THE DOOR IS A LARGE 1/1 HUNG WINDOW WITH SMALLER 1/1 HUNG FLANKERS.  A SOLDIER COURSE RUNS ALONG THE FACADE UNDER THE EAVES.  THE SECOND STORY HAS VINYL SIDING AND A FRONT-GABLED ROOF WITH GABLE RETURNS AND A KNEE BRACE AT THE APEX.  THERE ARE TWO 6/1 HUNG WINDOW ON THE SECOND STORY.  ON THE EAST ELEVATION, FIRST FLOOR IS A FIXED WINDOW WITH A BRICK SILL AND A SHED-ROOFED SECTION WITH THREE 1/1 HUNG WINDOWS, ALL WITH BRICK SILLS.  ON THE EAST ELEVATION, SECOND STORY ARE THREE 1/1 HUNG WINDOWS.  GARAGE WITH TWO SINGLE-CAR BAYS, OVERHEAD DOORS, AND FRONT-GABLED ROOF NORTH OF BUILDING.

THE DORMER HAS A ROW OF THREE AWNING WINDOWS WITH WIDE TRIM.  BELOW EACH WINDOW IS AN INTEGRAL PLANTER.  ON THE WEST ELEVATION ARE THREE WINDOWS ON THE GROUND FLOOR AND ONE ON THE 1 1/2 FLOOR. EXTER_FEA: TWO STORIES; FULL WIDTH PORCH; TRELLISED PORCH
DEC_DETAIL: EXPOSED ROOF BEAMS; STUCCO PIERS; EXPOSED RATER TAILS; OPEN EAVES
DES_RES: TWO STORY STUCCOED CRAFTSMAN.  A SET OF CONCRETE STEPS FLANKED ON THE EAST AND WEST SIDES BY A LOW STUCCOED WALL WITH CAPSTONES LEADS UP TO THE FULL-WIDTH PORCH.  A LARGE FRONT GABLE WITH TWO EXPOSED ROOF BEAMS, STUCCO AT THE GABLE END, AND A NESTLED GABLE ON THE WEST END COVERS THE BROAD PORCH.  THREE LARGE STUCCOED PIERS SUPPORT THE GABLED ROOF AND ARE INTEGRATED INTO A LOW RAILING THAT PARTIALLY ENCLOSES THE PORCH.  THE DOOR IS FLANKED ON THE EAST SIDE BY A ROW OF THREE 4/1 HUNG COTTAGE WINDOWS WITH WIDE TRIM.  WEST OF THE DOOR IS A TRELLISED PORCH ADDITION THAT CONNECTS TO THE ORIGINAL PORCH AND HAS TWO STUCCOED PIER SUPPORTS.  ON THE HIPPED-ROOFED SECOND STORY ARE TWO HUNG WINDOWS AND A SMALLER AWNING WINDOW.  ON THE WEST ELEVATION, GROUND FLOOR, IS THE TRELLISED PORCH AND A LARGE 8/1 HUNG COTTAGE WINDOW.  SOUTH OF THE WINDOW IS A FRONT-GABLED SECTION WITH A ROW OF THREE HUNG COTTAGE WINDOWS.  THE LARGER, CENTRAL, 6/1 HUNG WINDOW IS FLANKED ON EITHER SIDE BY A 4/1 HUNG WINDOW.  SOUTH OF THIS SECTION IS ARE TWO HUNG WINDOWS SEPARATED BY A HIPPED SECTION WITH A 4/1 HUNG COTTAGE WINDOW.  ON THE WEST ELEVATION, SECOND FLOOR, IS A CENTRAL HIPPED SECTION WITH THREE 3/1 HUNG COTTAGE WINDOWS FLANKED ON THE SOUTH SIDE BY A HIPPED SECTION WITH THREE 9/1 HUNG WINDOWS AND ON THE NORTH BY A HIPPED SECTION WITH TWO HUNG WINDOWS.   	SINGLE STORY GARAGE SOUTH OF MAIN BUILDING. SOUTH OF BUILDING IS A GARAGE WITH HIPPED ROOF, SINGLE CAR BAY, AND PANELED OVERHEAD DOOR, AND A 4/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOW ON WEST ELEVATION. ON THE NORTH ELEVATION IS A PANELED DOOR WITH A SQUARE WINDOW AND ANOTHER 4/1 HUNG WOOD WINDOW.

DOC_SOURCE: SANBORN 1922; SANBORN 1922-1955
EXTER_FEA: TWO STORY PORCHES; RECESSED ENTRY
DEC_DETAIL: BALUSTERS; FRIEZE; RECESSED ENTRY DETAILS
DES_RES: THIS TWO STORY BRICK BUILDING THREE BAYS WIDE. THE CENTER BAY IS RECESSED AND FEATURES A CURVED CANOPY OVER THE ENTRY WHICH IS A MULTI-PANE WOOD DOOR WITH TWO TWELVE PANE SIDELIGHTS. ABOVE THE ENTRY, ON THE SECOND FLOOR ARE THREE MULTI-PANE OVER ONE WINDOWS. THE FIRST AND THIRD BAYS PROJECT FROM THE FACADE. THE FIRST FLOOR IS AN ENCLOSED PORCH WITH FIVE ONE-OVER-ONE HUNG WINDOWS ON THE FACADE AND TWO ONE-OVER-ONE WINDOWS ON EACH SIDE. EACH WINDOW HAS A STONE SILL. THE SECOND FLOOR HAS WOOD BALUSTERS AND THE WALL IS SET FLUSH WITH THE FACADE CREATING AN OPEN SLEEPING PORCH. THE SECOND FLOOR HAS FOUR MULTI-PANE-OVER-ONE HUNG WINDOWS AND AN ENTRY DOOR. THE ENTIRE FACADE HAS A LARGE FRIEZE DETAIL. THE SOUTH ELEVATION HAS THREE MULTI-PANE-OVER-ONE WINDOWS ON THE FIRST AND SECOND FLOORS AT THE SOUTHWEST CORNER. THE REMAINDER OF THE SOUTH ELEVATION HAS TWO SMALL FIXED PANE WINDOWS ON BOTH THE FIRST AND SECOND FLOORS. THE NORTH ELEVATION CANNOT BE SEEN DUE TO AN ADJACENT BUILDING AND VEGETATION.
COMMENTS: SECONDARY STRUCTURE AT REAR OF PROPERTY THAT CANNOT BE SEEN FROM THE STREET

desc_seg: WARRANTS FURTHER STUDY AS A CONTRIBUTING RESOURCE IN THE HERITAGE HILLS EAST HISTORIC DISTRICT
DOC_SOURCE: SANBORN 1922; SANBORN 1922-1955
EXTER_FEA: ELABORATE ENTRY; SECOND STORY BALCONY
DEC_DETAIL: TRANSOM; SECOND STORY ENTRY; CARTOUCHE
DES_RES: THIS TWO STORY BRICK HOUSE HAS A CENTRAL ENTRY FEATURING DOUBLE PANE AND PANEL DOORS AND A STARBURST GLASS TRANSOM WINDOW. THE ENTRY HAS A NARROW PORCH WITH A FLAT ROOF THAT HAS A NARROW FRIEZE AND IS SUPPORTED BY NARROW COMPOSITE COLUMNS. THE ROOF OF THE PORCH CREATES A BALCONY FOR THE SECOND FLOOR WHICH IS SURROUNDED AT THE EDGE BY METAL RAILINGS AND NEWEL POSTS. THE BALCONY IS ACCESSED BY TWO FOUR PANE CASEMENT WINDOWS WITH SIDELIGHTS AND A CARTOUCHE ON EITHER SIDE OF THE SIDELIGHTS. ON THE FIRST FLOOR, ON EITHER SIDE OF THE ENTRY, ARE TWO SIX-OVER-SIX HUNG WINDOWS WITH STONE SILLS AND LINTELS AND A CAST FAN TRANSOM WITH A BRICK ARCH AND STONE KEYSTONE. THE SECOND FLOOR HAS TWO SIX-OVER-SIX HUNG WINDOWS WITH STONE SILLS AND METAL RAILINGS ON EITHER SIDE OF THE BALCONY. THE SOUTH ELEVATION CANNOT BE SEEN DUE TO AN ADJACENT BUILDING. THE NORTH ELEVATION HAS A PANEL DOOR AND A FIXED PANE WINDOW SHELTERED BY A HIPPED ROOF WITH BRACKETS AND A SIX-OVER-SIX HUNG WINDOW WITH STONE SILL AND LINTEL AND A CAST STONE FAN TRANSOM WITH A BRICK ARCH AND STONE KEYSTONE ON THE FIRST FLOOR. THE SECOND FLOOR HAS A SIX-OVER-SIX-OVER-SIX HUNG WINDOW WITH A THREE PANE TRANSOM AND A LOUVERED VENT WITH A BRICK TRANSOM. EACH HAS A STONE SILL AND LINTEL WITH A BRICK ARCH AND STONE KEYSTONE. ALL OF THESE ARE LOCATED IN THE GABLE END OF THE NORTH ELEVATION. THE SIDE GABLE WING HAS EIGHT SIX-OVER-SIX HUNG WINDOWS WITH STONE SILLS ON THE FIRST FLOOR. THE SECOND FLOOR HAS SEVEN SIX-OVER-SIX HUNG WINDOWS WITH STONE SILLS AND A NARROW FIXED PANE WINDOW ON THE SECOND FLOOR.
CONTINUATION: AT THE REAR OF THE PROPERTY IS A THREE BAY WIDE, ONE STORY GARAGE. THE WALLS ARE CLAD OF BRICK AND THE END WALLS EXTEND ABOVE THE FLAT ROOF. THE DOUBLE GARAGE DOORS ARE LOCATED ON THE EAST ELEVATION.

DES_RES: THIS ONE-STORY GAS STATION BUILDING IS RECTANGULAR SHAPED, WITH ONE OF THE NARROW ENDS ROUNDED. THIS ROUNDED END FACES NORTHEAST, THE CORNER OF SE 15TH ST. AND VICKIE DR. THE CANOPY EXTENDS OUT IN TWO DIRECTIONS FROM THIS ROUNDED BAY. EAST TO VICKIE DR. AND NORTH TO SE 15TH. A DOORWAY IN A WALL OF GLASS WITH WOOD WAINSCOT IS UNDER EACH WING OF THE CANOPY. A DECORATIVE MANSARD ROOF IS ON THE SOUTHEAST AND NORTHWEST FACADES, BEHIND THE ROUNDED BAY.
COMMENTS: TAX ASSESSOR RECORDS GIVE 1967 AS THE CONSTRUCTION DATE, AND 1974 AS THE DATE OF REMODELING IT IS IN AN AREA THAT IS NOT PLATTED.

DEC_DETAIL: CANOPIES
DES_RES: THIS TWO-STORY BUILDING FACES EAST ONTO BROADWAY. IT FEATURES A CENTRAL ENTRY WITH A TRANSOM WINDOW AND A LARGE PLATE GLASS WINDOW. ON EITHER SIDE OF THE ENTRY IS A NINE-PANE PLATE GLASS WINDOW. AT THE SOUTHEAST CORNER IS AN ADDITIONAL ENTRY WITH A TRANSOM. THE LARGE WINDOW AT THE NORTHEAST CORNER ALSO HAS IN FRONT OF IT, A LARGE PLANTER. BETWEEN THE FIRST AND SECOND FLOOR IS A LARGE FLAT CANOPY. THE SECOND FLOOR IS SET BACK SLIGHTLY FROM THE FIRST. THE SECOND FLOOR HAS NINE THREE PANE WINDOWS. ABOVE THE WINDOWS IS A FLAT ROOF CANOPY. THE PARAPET IS DESIGNED IN THE SAME MATERIAL AS THE CANOPIES. THE NORTH ELEVATION HAS THREE FIXED PANE WINDOWS THAT FOLLOW AN INTERIOR STAIRCASE. THE SECOND FLOOR HAS THREE TWO PANE SLIDING WINDOWS. THE WEST PORTION OF THE NORTH ELEVATION HAS EIGHT FIXED PANE WINDOWS ON THE SECOND FLOOR.

THIS SECTION INCLUDING THE FIRST FLOOR IS SLIGHTLY RECESSED. THE NORTH ELEVATION HAS THREE SETS OF TWO ONE-OVER-ONE WINDOWS WITH STONE SILLS ON BOTH THE FIRST AND SECOND FLOORS.

DEC_DETAIL: INTEGRAL PLANTERS; CAPSTONES
DES_RES: TWO STORY BUILDING WITH BRICK VENEER. FOUR STEPS LEAD UP TO THE FULL-WIDTH ENTRY PORCH ON THE GROUND LEVEL.  A LOW BRICK WALL WITH A CAPSTONE AND INTEGRAL PLANTER LINES THE STEPS ON THE NORTH AND SOUTH SIDES.  THERE ARE TWO DOORS, EACH SLAB WITH THREE PANES, ON THE PORCH'S NORTH END.  SOUTH OF THE DOORS IS A LARGE 1/1 HUNG WINDOW WITH SMALLER 1/1 HUNG FLANKERS AND BRICK SILL.  A LOW BRICK WALL WITH CAPSTONE PARTIALLY ENCLOSES THE PORCH.  THE WALL CONNECTS THREE BRICK PIERS, WHICH EXTEND THROUGH THE SECOND STORY TO SUPPORT THE MAIN HIPPED ROOF.  A WOODEN RAIL RUNS ALONG THE SECOND FLOOR BALCONY.  THE SECOND FLOOR ALSO HAS A SLAB DOOR WITH THREE PANES AND A LARGE 1/1 HUNG WINDOW WITH SMALLER 1/1 HUNG FLANKERS.
